func SafetyResultsToProto(flags []SafetyFlagResult) []*specv1.SafetyFlag {
    out[i] = &specv1.SafetyFlag{
        Severity: severityToProto[f.Severity],  // zero value = UNSPECIFIED if key missing
```

If a new FindingSeverity constant is added to safety.go without updating severityToProto, the resulting proto will have FINDING_SEVERITY_UNSPECIFIED (0) instead of a meaningful severity. This failure is completely silent — no log, no error, no panic. The caller sees a safety flag with severity UNSPECIFIED and no indication of a mapping problem.

