File: cmd/specgraph/serve.go, line 327

The bootstrapConstitution function returns nil (with //nolint:nilerr comment) for any os.ReadFile error, not just file-not-found. This means permission errors, disk I/O failures, and path errors are silently swallowed and treated as 'no YAML file present':

    data, err := os.ReadFile(yamlPath)
    if err != nil {
        return nil //nolint:nilerr // no YAML file is expected and acceptable
    }

This is overly broad. Only os.IsNotExist errors should be ignored. A permission denied error or corrupt FS would cause a silent skip of constitution bootstrapping with no diagnostic. This is compounded by serve.go line 283 which only logs a warning for bootstrapConstitution failures, meaning even properly returned errors do not halt startup.

Suggested fix:
