File: cmd/specgraph/cmd_test.go

Eight tests across 106 lines follow a copy-paste pattern — every funnel command (spark, shape, specify, decompose) gets an identical pair: RequiresSlug and AcceptsSlug, then one flag-registration test each. Each test body is 5–8 lines of identical boilerplate.

Example (all four require-slug tests are structurally identical):

    func TestShapeCmd_RequiresSlug(t *testing.T) {
        err := shapeCmd.Args(shapeCmd, []string{})
        if err == nil { t.Fatal("expected error when slug arg is missing") }
        if !strings.Contains(err.Error(), "accepts 1 arg") {
