message AmendRequest {
  string slug = 1;
  string reason = 2;
  string target_stage = 3;   // <-- should be AuthoringStage
}

The AuthoringStage enum is defined earlier in the same proto file (lines 10-16). Using string for target_stage means any client can pass an arbitrary value. The handler in authoring_handler.go:170 passes this string directly to store.AmendSpec which then calls authoring.ValidateTransition at runtime. The enum would catch the invalid value at the protobuf deserialization boundary.

